UK- Based Nigerian singer and record label owner, Segun Olufowobi aka Whytepatch has said that his encounter with an unknown lady in a cab raised his hopes musically. Whytepatch noted that he was on the verge of giving up when he met the said lady who encouraged him and told him never to give up on his chosen career. “I have been through situations in my career that feels like I was about to hit it off and was discouraged in the past to quit music aside being a producer. But an encounter with a lady in the cab years ago urged me to go ahead and dust off the negative feeling”, he said.   Biodun Stephen’s Strangers set for cinema debut     AFRIFF calls for entry ahead of 11th edition     Falz laments insecurity, poor electricity, others   With years of experience as an artiste and a producer, Whytepatch who recently visited Nigeria where had a media parley revealed that he recently released an 8 track Extended Play (EP) which according to him is a reflection of his journey in the music industry over the years. ‘Dust Off’ according to the charismatic music artist, who recorded a Grammy Award nomination credit with a group, ‘5 Star’, was inspired by the need to soldier on and dust off the negative vibes and let downs that may want him not to be at his best in life. Speaking further, Whytepatch also disclosed that he is set for a music tour in Kenya, Tanzania and in Europe where his music is being felt. Whytepatch is best known across Europe where he peaked the dance charts at number 2  across Europe with a dance tune called  ‘See You Dance’.ft. Andriah Arrindell.